Class AdobeAssetFolder

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.storage.controllers.upload.UploadDestination<AdobeAssetFolder>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AdobeAssetPackage

    public class AdobeAssetFolder
extends AdobeAsset
implements com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.internal.storage.controllers.upload.UploadDestination<AdobeAssetFolder>
    AdobeAssetFolder represents a folder in the Creative Cloud and provides access to folder contents in pages of data as well as provisions for creating and deleting folders. Folder items are fetched from Creative Cloud in pages, so the field on which the items should be sorted as well as the sort direction must be specified when setting up this instance. If you need to change the sorting, you will need to create a new instance with the specified sort options. Once you have an AdobeAssetFolder instance set up, you can call hasNextPage and loadNextPage to start loading folder items from the Creative Cloud as needed.

      • getNextPage

        public void getNextPage(int pageSize,
                        IAdobeAssetFolderNextPageCallback nextPageDelegate)
        Asynchronously gets the next page of items from the cloud folder. This should only be called if hasNextPage returns true. Behavior is undefined if hasNextPage returned false.
        Parameters:
        pageSize - the number of items to be fetched. This is just a hint. The actual number fetched may be more or less than this amount.
        nextPageDelegate - IAdobeAssetFolderNextPageCallback handler to handle completion, error for request.

      • resetPaging

        public void resetPaging()
        Resets the page iterator so that any subsequent call to hasNextPage will return true, and getNextPage will return the first page of cloud items. Keeps the current sorting options in effect.

      • resetPagingOrderedByField

        Parameters:
        field - the field on which the items in the folder will be sorted (e.g., name, modification date).
        direction - the direction (ascending or descending) in the the items will be sorted.
